----- stdout -----
Analyze a module and report all internal crate references

Usage: crawk use [OPTIONS] <MODULE_PATH>

Arguments:
  <MODULE_PATH>  Module path relative to the crate root (e.g., "utils" or "foo::bar::baz")

Options:
  -r, --recursive        Recursively analyze all submodules (disabled by default)
  -t, --include-tests    Include modules defined in `#[cfg(test)]` blocks (excluded by default)
  -e, --expand           Expand grouped imports into individual paths
  -d, --depth <DEPTH>    Truncate displayed dependency paths to at most N segments.
                         Paths with ≤N segments are shown unchanged. After truncation,
                         duplicates are removed and the result is sorted.
  -f, --format <FORMAT>  Output format [default: plain] [possible values: plain, grouped]
  -G, --resolve-globs    Resolve glob imports (`use crate::foo::*`) to explicit items
  -h, --help             Print help (see more with '--help')

----- stderr -----
